Vulnerable post —> PLEASE SHARE! Last week I found out several of my designs have been STOLEN by @sheinofficial and are being sold without my permission on their site, even though all of my work is protected by US copyright. This is absolutely devastating and heartbreaking.  My lawyer has reached out to Shein to no avail. We haven’t even received so much as a response from them. Apparently they don’t follow US copyright laws since they are based in China. After digging into this I’ve found it is commonplace for Shein to steal work from independent artists like myself.  I am posting here as a last resort to raise awareness and hopefully put pressure on them to take down my designs. I would ask that you please share this post and tag them! @sheinofficial It’s absolutely despicable that you steal work from small businesses who don’t have the resources to fight you.  Thanks for being here friends! I am truly so grateful for each and everyone of you. Thank you to those who reached out letting me know my work had been stolen.  This business means everything to me and it is only possible because of you, my customers and friends.  #sheinsteals #boycottshein @shein_official @shein_us

Zara released a statement, after publication, Tuesday expressing regret for the “misunderstanding” where “unfortunately, some customers felt offended” by the ads and “saw … something far from what was intended.” The campaign for the Atelier line, titled “Collection 04_The Jacket,” features model Kristen McMenamy standing in front of props including mannequins without limbs wrapped in white plastic surrounded by rubble. Other models behind her were covered in dust and dressed in white. Pro-Palestinian supporters compared the wrapped mannequins to the body bags used for Palestinians in Gaza killed in the war against Israel. #hidesidemagazine ✨✨
